Mr Rakonczay said that in his solitude he often thought about what his loved ones were likely going through, and was heartened by the faith and confidence of his family in his abilities during the long silence.

'I was positively surprised in those at home ... because everyone was certain that if I run into any difficulties, I'll be able to solve them,' Mr Rakonczay said.

'It was a great relief to reach port because it meant completing the journey and because my family could finally know for sure that I was OK.'

While he lit smoke flares on three separate occasions to signal ships passing nearby, he was not able to communicate with any of them.

